    "description": "ICICI Direct Holdings Services invites applications from qualified candidates for the position of Risk Analyst at our Varanasi location. This role offers excellent career advancement prospects.\n\nAbout ICICI Direct Holdings Services:\nICICI Direct Holdings Services is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Implement and maintain internal controls and audit procedures\n• Manage accounts payable and accounts receivable functions\n• Monitor financial performance against targets and provide variance analysis\n• Coordinate with external auditors during annual audits\n• Prepare and analyze financial statements, reports, and budgets\n• Maintain general ledger and ensure accurate bookkeeping\n• Manage credit risk assessment and loan appraisal processes\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Sc / M.Sc in Life Sciences\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Financial Modeling\n• Proficiency in Python for Finance\n• Proficiency in Budgeting\n• Proficiency in Tally\n• Proficiency in Bloomberg Terminal\n• Proficiency in Financial Reporting\n• Proficiency in SAP FICO\n• Proficiency in QuickBooks\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Flexible working hours\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Varanasi, Uttar Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with ICICI Direct Holdings Services!",
